Giving gizmos a list of connected keys. Current passing tests: 1.) Add trigger to an existing gizmo 2.) Do not add trigger to a non-existing gizmo
Refactored. No more tests. Map class for Triggers created
Removed add trigger methods from gizmos -all will be handled by one class

Merge branch 'refactorization' of https://gitlab.cis.strath.ac.uk/mhb15157/cs308-gizmoball into refactorization Changed the collision so the ball no longer slows to a stop and multiple balls no longer stick to one another - however we need to fix the amount of balls
# Conflicts: # src/controller/handlers/boardhandlers/ConnectTriggerHandler.java # src/controller/handlers/boardhandlers/DeleteHandler.java

Merge branch 'refactorization' of https://gitlab.cis.strath.ac.uk/mhb15157/cs308-gizmoball into refactorization also triggers with keys now work
# Conflicts: # src/controller/BuildController.java # src/controller/handlers/boardhandlers/ConnectTriggerHandler.java # src/model/GizmoballModel.java # src/model/board/gizmos/FlipperGizmo.java
Added save stuff to the exit and load handlers for when a board has not been saved and added todos for loading and saving key connect information
Added some error message functionality from the validation testing stuff, also modified some handlers to include buildcontroller for this

Move handler now moves balls and flippers, Load and save now handle connects keyconnects move gravity and friction, reset now works using save and load to a gamestate txt file to save the game state, added extra slider for friction (doesnt work yet, neither do the rest of the sliders), Appropriate buttons now get disabled on run of a game (all but stop and exit) and get enabled on stop of game (stop gets disabled), ball now checks its velocity and forces it to be between the min and max values, added a lighting class to make shapes look more 3d but its not working yet

Merge branch 'refactorization' of https://gitlab.cis.strath.ac.uk/mhb15157/cs308-gizmoball into refactorization
# Conflicts: # src/model/GizmoballModel.java
Added a list of all accepted keycode names as a txt file, for reference
Fixed an issue where board would clear things that are loaded in after clearing the current board
Fixed the error messages so they now appear for intersecting objects
Half-fixed shootBall - balls firing one at a time instead of all at once, but when a ball returns to the absorber, it takes all the other balls on the board with it, which messes up further firing
Just changed the extension to be gzb for gizmoball files
Added txt in again but as a second filter
